Overview
iOS Full SDK supports the following two main scenarios:

Audio/Video Communication
Audio/Video Live Broadcast
Known Issue and Limitation
To use the startAudioMixing API, ensure that the iOS device is >=8.0
Currently, encryption does not interoperate with the Web SDK (based on Web RTC).
Currently, it does not support the bluetooth on iPhone 8.
v1.14(Released Oct. 20th, 2017)
New Function

Added the API setAudioProfile() to set the audio parameters and scenarios;
Added the API setLocalVoicePitch() to set the local voice pitch;
Live Broadcast: added the API setInEarMonitoringVolume() to adjust the volume of the In-ear Monitor;
Improvement

Optimized the audio experience at high bitrate;
Live Broadcast: the audience can view the host within one sec in single-stream mode(938 ms on average, and 734 ms when in good network condition);
Save the bandwidth:
Before v1.14: If you choose not to hear the audio or view the video of a specific user, the network still sends the streams;
Starting from v1.14: If you choose not to hear the audio or view the video of a specific user, the network wonâ€™t send the stream of the user to save bandwidth;
Accurate control over bit rate:
Before v1.14: the inaccurate control over bitrate often causes huge flunctuation, which leads to network congestion and higher rate of packet loss and frame loss. It affects the accuracy of the bandwidth estimation module especially when the network is in unsatisfying condition;
Starting from v1.14: the accurate control over bitrate avoids huge flunctuation to avoid network congestion and shorten the transmission latency. Contact sales@agora.io for details if required;
Bug Fix:

Fixed the occasional crashes on certaion iOS devices.

